        "The ACLUF's strength lies in its institutional maturity and strategic grantmaking. By distributing <cite id=\"7\">$24.4 million to 62 domestic recipients</cite>, it empowers local affiliates to tackle regional civil rights issues. This is complemented by a <cite id=\"12\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, reflecting a high level of public disclosure regarding its goals and metrics. Furthermore, the foundation's governance is supported by a <cite id=\"13\">100% independent board of 13 members</cite>, ensuring objective oversight of its <cite id=\"14\">$828.6 million in total assets</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "The American Civil Liberties Union Foundation, Inc. (ACLUF) is a cornerstone of American legal advocacy, dedicated to defending constitutional rights through <cite id=\"1\">high-impact litigation and systemic reform</cite>. Founded in <cite id=\"2\">1920</cite>, the organization has spent over a century litigating landmark cases that define individual liberties in the United States. In the 2024 fiscal year, the foundation reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $185,146,988</cite>, primarily driven by <cite id=\"4\">$169.1 million in public contributions</cite>. The ACLUF operates as the 501(c)(3) arm of the ACLU, focusing on <cite id=\"5\">immigrants' rights, reproductive freedom, and racial justice</cite> through a network of state affiliates and national projects. Its financial structure is characterized by significant stability, maintaining <cite id=\"6\">40.5 months of working capital</cite> to sustain long-term legal battles. The organization is a prolific grantmaker, distributing <cite id=\"7\">$24.4 million in domestic grants</cite> to support local advocacy, including over <cite id=\"8\">$2 million to the ACLU Foundation of Louisiana</cite>. By combining direct litigation with capacity building for state-level initiatives, the foundation ensures a multi-tiered defense of civil liberties across all <cite id=\"9\">50 states and US territories</cite>.",
